The paper discusses the use of machine learning to predict the solution value of a difficult combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem also involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), robotics (cs.RO), and computational engineering (cs.CE) as it has industrial applications in the cutting stock problem.
